    },
    {
      "id": "5a6e45a4_5982ae65",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/sync/lcm/CmHandleStateMonitor.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "I don't agree.\n\ninitialiseCmHandleStateMonitor method in CmHandleStateMonitor, should run before CmHandleStateGaugeConfig is created so that cmHandlesByState map being populated with stateMetricKey. \n\ncmHandlesByState.putIfAbsent(stateMetricKey, cmHandleCountForState);\n\nAfter this methot being run, the gauges should kick off to create the beans by looking up cmHandlesByState. \n\n\nGauge.builder(CM_HANDLE_STATE_GAUGE, cmHandlesByState,\n                value -> cmHandlesByState.get(\"advisedCmHandlesCount\")",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 8063,
        "name": "Halil Cakal",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "halil.cakal@est.tech",
        "username": "halil.cakal"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-26 16:11:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "97430306_333ae4ee",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "3c3ea5d4_f8e829c0",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/sync/lcm/CmHandleStateMonitor.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 41,
      "message": "Sorry, I'm mistaken. The Monitor actually initializes the values which need to be returned by the Gauge. So the correct flow is:\n\n    CmHandleStateGaugeConfig depends on CmHandleStateMonitor depends on AdminCacheConfig\n\nwhich is what is implemented.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
